    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc_es.00079.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>   
                <handShift rend="printed"/>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">D. G. BRINTON, M.D.,<lb/>115 SOUTH SEVENTH STREET,<lb/>
                     PHILADELPHIA.</name>
                    <name type="place">The Medical and Surgical Reporter (Weekly,)<lb/>The Compendium of Medical Science (Quarterly),<lb/>
                    AND OTHER<lb/> MEDICAL AND SCIENTIFIC PUBLICATIONS.</name>
                    <handShift rend="manuscript"/>
                    <date when="1887-02-28">Feby 28,<handShift rend="printed"/> 1887.<ptr
                            target="loc.06061_n1"/></date> 
                    <handShift rend="manuscript"/>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My dear Mr. Whitman:</salute>  
            </opener>
            <p>I wish to express to you the great satisfaction, which I have heard on all hands,
                felt by the members of the Club at your reading, and remarks, on last Tuesday
                    evening.<ptr target="loc.06061_n2"/></p>
            <p>Your selections were most happy, and your rendering of them impressive. Every one
                present, both members and guests, with whom I have spoken about it, has regarded it
                as a memorable occasion, and a thoroughly successful meeting.</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>With best wishes I remain yours sincerely</salute>
                <signed>D. G. Brinton</signed>
            </closer>
